  Locus:
    Page: 118
    Verse: 11
Tags:
  - Ego/Vanity
---
The ego endlessly pulls us from one burning desire to another. Somehow the
ego wishes to impose its will on events, to pretend that its needs, its
plans are the most important, that it knows all, and knows what is best for
us.
